events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — LeBron James just put his head down and repeatedly drove to the basket Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James closes in on scoring record, Lakers rally past Pacers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell took his most vicious shots at Dillon Brooks after the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs All-Star Mitchell calls Grizzlies' Brooks dirty player

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett never gave his coach a chance to sit him for long Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 30, helps Knicks hold off Heat 106-104

headlines.description: — Ayo Dosunmu matched a season high with 22 points, Coby White scored 20 points and the Chicago Bulls overcame shaky outings by DeMar DeRozan and Zach LaVine to beat the Charlotte Hornets 114-98 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dosunmu, White lead way as Bulls beat Hornets 114-98

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — The Dallas Mavericks barely held on after leading by 27 points when Luka Doncic exited the game with a right heel injury on a hard fall.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs hang on after Doncic hurt, hand Pels 10th straight loss

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray just nodded when asked if this might be the most confident he’s ever been.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic lead charge as Nuggets beat Warriors 134-117

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo celebrated his most famous 50-point performance by ordering 50 chicken nuggets at a Chick-fil-A drive-through the next day.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 54 points, Bucks beat Clippers 106-105
